{
  "doc_id": "21497",
  "text": "In univariable and multivariable analyses melanoma was significantly associated with a history of prostate cancer. Androgens have long been implicated in prostatic carcinogenesis and thus, androgen deprivation is the mainstay of prostate cancer treatment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . An example of the pathophysiologic relationship is illustrated in severe acne, an inflammatory androgen-induced condition which has been found to be significantly associated with increased risk of prostate cancer [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
